# Premium UI Foundations

## Golden Rule: Luxury = Restraint

**Premium UIs feel expensive because they use space, typography, and color with discipline. Every pixel matters.**

**See also**:
- @37-premium-ui-visual-design.mdc - Colors, surfaces, borders
- @37-premium-ui-components.mdc - Buttons, inputs, motion
- @37-premium-ui-implementation.mdc - Accessibility, tokens, checklists

---

## 1. Layout and Spacing Rules

### 1.1 8pt Grid System (MANDATORY)

**Rule**: Use an 8pt grid everywhere. No exceptions.

**Reference**: @src/shared/constants/spacing.ts

**Allowed spacing tokens ONLY**:
```typescript
export const SPACING = {
  0: 0,
  1: 4,   // 0.5 × 8
  2: 8,   // 1 × 8
  3: 12,  // 1.5 × 8
  4: 16,  // 2 × 8
  5: 20,  // 2.5 × 8
  6: 24,  // 3 × 8
  8: 32,  // 4 × 8
  10: 40, // 5 × 8
  12: 48, // 6 × 8
} as const;
```

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: Random spacing values (14, 18, 22, 26, 28, 30, 34, 36, 38, 42, 44, 46, etc.)

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
padding: SPACING[4],        // 16px
marginBottom: SPACING[6],    // 24px
gap: SPACING[2],            // 8px
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
padding: 14,                // Not in 8pt grid!
marginBottom: 18,           // Not in 8pt grid!
gap: 22,                    // Not in 8pt grid!
```

---

### 1.2 Screen and Card Padding

**Screen Padding**:
- **Compact**: `SPACING[4]` (16px) - for dense information screens
- **Premium feel**: `SPACING[5]` (20px) - default for most screens

**Card Padding**:
- **Minimum**: `SPACING[3]` (12px) - never less
- **Standard**: `SPACING[4]` (16px) - default
- **Premium**: `SPACING[5]` (20px) - for important cards

---

### 1.3 Vertical Rhythm (Premium Air)

**Rule**: Prefer fewer, larger gaps. Premium UIs use air.

**Spacing Guidelines**:
- **Between major sections**: `SPACING[8]` (32px) to `SPACING[10]` (40px)
- **Between related items**: `SPACING[3]` (12px) to `SPACING[4]` (16px)
- **Between label and value**: `SPACING[1]` (4px) to `SPACING[2]` (8px)

---

### 1.4 Alignment is Non-Negotiable

**Rule**: All text baselines align. Icons align to text centerline system-wide.

**Text Baseline Alignment**:
```typescript
<View style={{ flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'baseline' }}>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.h1}>Title</Text>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.caption}>Subtitle</Text>
</View>
```

**Icon Alignment**:
```typescript
<View style={{ flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'center' }}>
  <Icon size={20} />
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.body}>Label</Text>
</View>
```

